name: Classic Waffles
prepTime: 10 minutes
cookTime: 15 minutes
portions: 4
hint: Using a second bowl is entirely optional. I ususally make a well in the dry ingredients and mix everything together at once.
source: http://allrecipes.com/recipe/20513/classic-waffles/

ingredients:
  - (2 cups)	All-purpose flour
  - (1 tsp)	Salt
  - (4 tsp)	Baking powder
  - (2 tbsp)	Sugar     
  - (2)		Eggs
  - (1.5 cups)	Milk
  - (1/3 cups)	Butter, melted
  - (1 tsp)	Vanilla extract

steps:
  - In a large mixing bowl, combine dry ingredients
  - In a seperate (large) mixing bowl, combine liquid ingredients
  - Mix liquid ingredients quickly into dry ingredients
  - Spoon batter into preheated waffle iron. Cook until golden. Serve
    immediately.
